text=## Top-Level Directories\n\n**Main directories:**\n- `crates/` — Rust source code modules\n- `UI/` — Web interface files\n- `configs/` — Configuration files\n- `docker/` — Docker-related files\n- `docs/` — Documentation\n- `scripts/` — Utility scripts\n- `services/` — Service-related files\n- `target/` — Build output\n\n**Supporting directories:**\n- `data/` — Data storage\n- `logs/` — Log files\n- `migrations/` — Database migrations\n- `node_modules/` — Node.js dependencies\n- `plans/` — Project plans\n- `prompts/` — Prompt templates\n- `skills_output/` — Skill outputs\n- `systemd/` — Systemd service files\n- `external_skills/` — External skill files\n\n**Hidden directories:** `.cargo/`, `.git/`\n\n---\n\n**Beginner-friendly explanation:**\n\nThink of this project like a toolbox: `crates/` holds the core Rust code that powers everything, `UI/` contains the website interface you interact with, `configs/` and `services/` store the settings to connect to platforms like Telegram and WhatsApp, `scripts/` provides quick commands to start/stop things, and `docker/` lets you run everything in containers for easy deployment.

